<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1869,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,1869,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the ex-president of republic of 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1070,1869,1895]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<date box="[1085,1218,1869,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1922-11-15">11/15/1922</date>
until 
<date box="[1286,1422,1869,1895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1926-11-15">11/15/1926</date>
), Arthur da Silva Bernardes, born in Viçosa (MG), and founder of the Escola Superior de Agricultura e Veterinária—ESAV, that later came to be know as the Universidade Federal de Viçosa—UFV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
